The paper proposes robust adaptive beamforming techniques based on shrinkage methods, which are commonly used in signal processing and statistical learning. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses computational complexity, which suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the simulations and comparisons with existing techniques indicate a possible fit with cs.SP (Speech Processing).
